The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Coppola to get lifetime Oscar
                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Coppola to get lifetime Oscar
                            
	Los Angeles, Aug. 26 (Reuters): Godfather director Francis Ford Coppola is to get a lifetime achievement Oscar to add to his stack of five Academy Awards, the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences said yesterday.        
	Coppola, 71, who also wrote and directed the Vietnam war movie Apocalypse Now, will receive the Irving Thalberg Memorial Award. It will be handed out at a dinner in November in Los Angeles.         
	The lifetime achievement nod is given toa creative producer whose body of work reflects a consistently high quality of motion picture production.                                                                                                                                                           
